New Jersey Shipbuilding & Dredging Company, Libelant-Appellee, v. Steam Tug ENERGY, Her Engines, etc.; James Hughes, Jr., Claimant-Appellant. Circuit Court of Appeals, Second Circuit. May 2, 1927. No. 293. Barry, Wainwright, Thacher & Symmers, of New York City (James K. Symmers and Earle Farwell, both of New York City, of counsel), for appellant. Alexander & Ash, of New York City (Peter Alexander, of New York City, of counsel), for appellee.

before MANTON and SWAN, Circuit Judges, and CAMPBELL, District Judge.

PER CURIAM.

Decree affirmed, with costs.
